}}'''Isa Pola''' (19 December 1909 – 17 December 1984) was an Italian stage and film actress. She appeared in  more than thirty films during her career. One of her earliest screen roles was the female lead in ''[[Steel (1933 film)|Steel]]'' (1933), a realist film set in the steelworking industry.<ref>Landy p.185</ref>

==Selected filmography==
* ''[[The Song of Love (1930 film)|The Song of Love]]'' (1930)
* ''[[Mother Earth (film)|Mother Earth]]'' (1931)
* ''[[The Opera Singer]]'' (1932)
* ''[[The Last Adventure (1932 film)|The Last Adventure]]'' (1932)
* ''[[La Wally (film)|La Wally]]'' (1932)
* ''[[The Telephone Operator (1932 film)|The Telephone Operator]]'' (1932)
* ''[[Steel (1933 film)|Steel]]'' (1933)
* ''[[Creatures of the Night (film)|Creatures of the Night]]'' (1934)
* ''[[The Anonymous Roylott]]'' (1936)
* ''[[It Was I!]]'' (1937)
* ''[[The Widow (1939 film)|The Widow]]'' (1939)
* ''[[Lucrezia Borgia (1940 film)|Lucrezia Borgia]]'' (1940)
* ''[[Bridge of Glass (film)|Bridge of Glass]]'' (1940)
* ''[[Girl of the Golden West (film)|Girl of the Golden West]]'' (1942)
* ''[[The Children Are Watching Us]]'' (1944)
* ''[[Fury (1947 film)|Fury]]'' (1947)
* ''[[Margaret of Cortona (film)|Margaret of Cortona]]'' (1950)
* ''[[Ombre sul Canal Grande]]'' (1951)
* ''[[The Rival of the Empress]]'' (1951)
* ''[[Three Forbidden Stories]]'' (1952)
* ''[[The Queen of Sheba (1952 film)|The Queen of Sheba]]'' (1952)

